                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Charleston</placeName>\n                                        <date>Jany 18<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1851</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p><addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>. Dr Sir. I have at<lb/> last\n                                        collected the amt due by <persName>I. I\n                                        Cohen</persName>,<lb/> and take pleasure in remitting Ck\n                                        for<lb/> $27.00 in full for the 3 subscriptions before<lb/>\n                                        alluded to. I begin to despair of <persName>Lewis<lb/>\n                                                  Levy</persName>, and would suggest that you write\n                                        him<lb/> a few lines requesting him to remit <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">me</hi><lb/> the amt of his dues,\n                                        as you have no agt<lb/> in <placeName>Augusta</placeName>,\n                                        and are anxious to collect all<lb/> outstanding debts. I can\n                                        see no other chance<lb/> of inducing him to make paymt.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Yr list has not increased much since<lb/> I last\n                                        wrote you, owing perhaps to want of<lb/> energy on my part.\n                                        I have been too busy to<lb/> bestow upon it the requisite\n                                        attention. Hereafter<lb/> I shall do better I hope. Mother\n                                        sends her<lb/> kind regards as do all of our family &amp;<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Aunts P &amp; R</persName> hope that you may\n                                        be<lb/> enabled to pay <placeName>Charleston</placeName> a\n                                        visit this<lb/> winter. We have here, a <persName>Mr E\n                                                  Hart</persName> of yr<lb/> city, Brother of\n                                                  <persName>Mr A Hart</persName>. He has recd<lb/>\n                                        some attention and appears to be a very<lb/> worthy young\n                                        man. <persName>Miss Isabel Moses</persName><lb/> has\n                                        returned to <placeName>Columbus</placeName>, having\n                                        heard<lb/> of the sudden death of her Sisters child,<lb/>\n                                        The <persName>Jenny Lind</persName> excitement drew a<lb/>\n                                        number of strangers to the city and made<lb/> our streets\n                                        gay and lively for some time.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v698z22/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
