                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v698z22/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>It is supposed that <persName>Mr Joshua Lazarus</persName>\n                                        will<lb/> be elected to the vacant Presidency of our<lb/>\n                                        congregation. <persName>Mr I\n                                                  Ottolengri<add>?</add></persName> has just been\n                                        made<lb/> Trustee. <persName>Rev Mr Rosenfeldt</persName>\n                                        has a call<lb/> from <placeName>California</placeName> which\n                                        he intends to accept<lb/> &amp; will leave for that region,\n                                        I am informed)<lb/> in a few weeks. His salary is to be\n                                        $4000<lb/> pr annum, which appears munificent<lb/> when\n                                        contrasted with the <hi rend=\"underline\">very\n                                        liberal</hi><lb/> provisions yr congregation made for\n                                        you<lb/> during yr ministration.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">We have not recd our number of the<lb/> Occident\n                                        for <date>Jany</date>, altho most of yr. Chas<lb/>\n                                        subscribers have theirs. Can you, without<lb/> inconvenience\n                                                  forw<hi rend=\"underline\">d</hi>\n                                        <persName>Mosher</persName> a duplicate<lb/> copy? I have\n                                        read yr address, however<lb/> which cannot, I am sure,\n                                        produce other<lb/> than a very favorable impression.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You may be assured that the Editor of<lb/> the\n                                        Asmonean is viewed in his true colors<lb/> by our community,\n                                        and that his assaults<lb/> upon you, have a reactionary\n                                        effect</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You have doubtless heard that some<lb/> difference\n                                        has arisen between <persName>Dr Eckman</persName><lb/> &amp;\n                                                  <persName>Mr Posnanski</persName> produced by\n                                        excited<lb/> controversial <sic>disenssions</sic>, and\n                                        this<lb/> difference has been enlarged and<lb/> aggravated\n                                        by the friends of either</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v698z22/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
